
[1]otherwise

   OTH'ERWISE, adv. [other and wise, manner.]

   1. In a different manner.

   Thy father was a worthy prince, and merited, alas! a better fate; but
   heaven thought otherwise.

   2. By other causes.

   Sir John Norris failed in the attempt of Lisborn, and returned with the
   loss, by sickness and otherwise, of 8000 men.

   3. In other respects.

   It is said truly, that the best men otherwise, are not always the best
   in regard to society.
